body: * Use lighter weight JRE for docker
* Internationalization has been added for the German language.
* Implement polyglot phrases for I18n
* Fix JAR duplication strategy
* Update Gradle, kotlin, kotlin-wrappers, ktor, and koin versions
* Add `-allow-example-urls` option
* When memory threshold is reached, re-initialize ValidationService

* Update to FHIR Core 5.6.55
* Fix IG dropdown interaction with simplifier.net [#83](https://github.com/hapifhir/org.hl7.fhir.validator-wrapper/issues/83)
* Automatic restart on OutOfMemory failures.

* Use JDK in docker image to inspect memory usage
* Improve description of free memory
* Use percentage based memory settings in docker java command
* Log validation request params
* Send GA event for validation
* Add google analytics
* Cleaned up unused code from prior to ace editor integration
* Fix core version in footer
* Fix core version in footer
* Fix core version in footer
* Automatically include FHIR core version in footer

* Add IG packages using simplifier.net API
* Fix inability to remove IGs from cliContext
* Reorganize FHIR version and IG selection options in UI
* Use npm package name instead of URL for selecting IGs
* Uploaded file validation now uses ace editor (https://ace.c9.io/)
* Add line numbers to uploaded file verification
* Update docker image to Java 11

* Drop to http for ig package server
* Update footer
* Remove bintray repositories from build
* updating fhir core version
* Upping validator version
* Fixed issue with version not being saved correctly if default version is used

* Changing default tx address
* Default desktop address fix
* Fixing issue 54 https://github.com/hapifhir/org.hl7.fhir.validator-wrapper/issues/54
* Added footer to website
* Added status icons to heard for tx server and packages server
